The paper deals with a game-theoretic model of estimation in the presence of strategic sensors, which involves information theory (cs.IT), game theory (cs.GT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the dynamic estimation problem, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and the use of equilibria in affine strategies, which is related to mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
